      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__timing__api__arch_1gad7a709477650c8596a96fe080f583fdd" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type><ref refid="include_2zephyr_2timing_2types_8h_1a08ae2ef7b1cd6f125db0cb548ea1f0e2" kindref="member">timing_t</ref></type>
        <definition>timing_t arch_timing_counter_get</definition>
        <argsstring>(void)</argsstring>
        <name>arch_timing_counter_get</name>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Return timing counter. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parblock><para></para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Any call to <ref refid="group__timing__api__arch_1gad7a709477650c8596a96fe080f583fdd" kindref="member">arch_timing_counter_get()</ref> must be done between calls to <ref refid="group__timing__api__arch_1gaf8cd88e81c2104b5eb0fbe42967b7834" kindref="member">arch_timing_start()</ref> and <ref refid="group__timing__api__arch_1ga566483c64f5c5d2f0465e3f969303fd3" kindref="member">arch_timing_stop()</ref>, and on the same CPU core.</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
</parblock></para>
<para><parblock><para></para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Not all architectures have a timing counter with 64 bit precision. It is possible to see this value &quot;go backwards&quot; due to internal rollover. Timing code must be prepared to address the rollover (with platform-dependent code, e.g. by casting to a uint32_t before subtraction) or by using <ref refid="group__timing__api__arch_1ga44d3a7bd8b7008c9cd6c0524e97f128c" kindref="member">arch_timing_cycles_get()</ref> which is required to understand the distinction.</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
</parblock></para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>Timing counter.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="group__timing__api_1gaa5736c87362de09749af1d8ff30b8208" kindref="member">timing_counter_get()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
